post_text: The Holdrege Girls’ Golf team took a trip to Cross Creek Golf Links in Cambridge on Monday. The varsity team shot a 219. They were led by Ella Jacobson with a 46, which was good for a tie for fourth. Hope Anderson had the second best score, carding a 53. Bailey Edgren led the JV team with a 73. The girls finished behind Broken Bow and Minden who shot 190 and 200 respectively. The Holdrege girls will travel next Tuesday to Minden for a 9-hole format tournament.
text: The Holdrege Girls’ Golf team took a trip to Cross Creek Golf Links in Cambridge on Monday. The varsity team shot a 219. They were led by Ella Jacobson with a 46, which was good for a tie for fourth. Hope Anderson had the second best score, carding a 53. Bailey Edgren led the JV team with a 73. The girls finished behind Broken Bow and Minden who shot 190 and 200 respectively. The Holdrege girls will travel next Tuesday to Minden for a 9-hole format tournament.

post_text:
Booster Club Stadium Seat Rentals

No more lugging heavy seats to cheer on the Dusters! The Holdrege Dusters Booster Club is now offering stadium seat rental at many Duster athletic events. For $5, fans can rent oversized stadium seats during the game and then return the seat when the game is over. Pictured from left are the generous stadium seat sponsors: Mark Reed, Reed Disposal; Phil Hinrichs, Farm Bureau Financial Services; Dr. Jeff Berney, Family Medical Specialties and Phelps Medical Group; Chadd Jacobson, Farmers National Company; and Greg Belgum, IES Commercial & Industrial. Not pictured is Ryan Bauer of Nelson-Bauer Funeral Homes and Aubri Nantkes, Screen Machine. Proceeds from stadium rental seats go to support Duster athletes and athletic programs. The booster club will also be selling hamburgers and hotdogs to hungry fans at all home varsity football games this fall along with Duster apparel, signs, blankets and masks.

Go Dusters!!!

Saturday morning retests since we had some tired guys from doubling up testing and conditioning this week. Two more guys broke over 8-0 in the broad jump along with this kid running a 4.83 laser 40 which is one of our more impressive performances on the guys side. When converted to handheld we are the talking the 4.55-4.6 range. The scary thing is once he fine tunes his sprint mechanics (straighten out his arm action) he is going to be even faster.

#DusterStrong

Fall Parent/Athlete/Coaches Meetings, from Mr. Schoneman:

On August 6th we will have coaches meeting with parents and athletes in separate areas of The High School and Tassel at 7:00 pm. We would like to limit the meetings to one parent per household, if possible.

Mr. Schoneman's portion of the meeting can be found here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IEY23ol9pGs&feature=youtu.be. We want to give our student/athletes the best chance to have fall activities.

Here are the places we will meet.

Football - Tassel Auditorium

Boys Tennis – Mrs. Clayton’s Room (Biology room, 1st floor)

Girls Golf – Mr. Hall’s Room (English room, near media center)

Cross Country – Mrs. Steinshouer's Room (Miss Stara’s, Math room)

Volleyball – HS Media Center

Softball – High School Mrs. Pearson’s Room (Math room)

If you have any questions or concerns please let Mr. Schoneman know.
Email: scott.schoneman@dusters.org
Phone: 995-6558

July 31 at 6:04 PM ·

Final summer attendance: 161 kids total 7-12, 86.49% attendance rate, 86.63% high school, 86.11% jr high. We had a close race for best team attendance with girls VB/BB edging football 89.88% to 89.82%!

101 athletes made over 85% of the workouts and 39 had perfect attendance.

I can’t say enough about the effort out of the kids. It speaks strongly to how much they want to improve athletically. Thank you to all of the coaches and administrators that made this possible!

#DusterStrong

shared_text:
Holdrege Middle School
July 23 at 7:58 PM ·

HMS will have an open house this year in place of our previous orientation nights. Due to the current circumstances, we don't want to put anyone into a situation where they are sitting shoulder to shoulder in the bleachers with hundreds of other patrons.

On Tuesday, August 11th we welcome you to stop by the middle school to pick up your child's schedule and say"Hi"to their teacher:)
From 6:00 - 7:00 pm 5th graders and students new to HMS may come in, pick up their schedule and walk through the building.
From 7:00 - 8:00 pm 6th, 7th and 8th grade students are welcome to pick up their schedules. This open house is not required. If you don't feel comfortable visiting that night, you may stop to pick up your child's schedule in the office on Wednesday or even wait until the first day of school. We can't wait to see you!

*Please limit the number of family members you bring with you.
*Masks are encouraged but not required.
*Please practice social distancing.

8:30-9:30 a.m.
10:00-11:00 a.m.
12:00-1:00 p.m.
1:30-2:30 p.m.
3:00-4:00 p.m.

Thank you.

post_text:
Drivers Education Information:

This is for students that have registered for Drivers Education.

The Safety Center has gotten the approval to hold the Holdrege 1 driver’s education class in-person. The class will still be held from June 1-5, 8am-12:30pm at Holdrege High School, Room 103. On-street driving will be scheduled during the afternoons and evenings June 1-5 and will continue until all students have driven. Please send a mask with your child every day to both classroom instruction and driving appointments. The classroom will be sanitized after each classroom session and hand sanitizer will be available for use. The students will practice social distancing while in the classroom by sitting 6 feet apart. The car will also be sanitized after each student completes a driving appointment.

Please contact the Safety Center with any questions.

Thanks!

post_text:
Sports Physicals Information, from Mr. Schoneman:

Holdrege Public School 2019-20 Pre-Participation Physical Exams (PPE) will be ACCEPTED for the 2020-21 school year. You will NOT need to get a new physical if you are a returning 9,10,11 grader.

The requirement for students entering the7th grade to have a physical exam is Nebraska state education law and we do not have the ability to waive that requirement. However, the physicals that the current 7th graders have for the 2019-2020 school year can be used for NSAA purposes for the 2020-2021 school year.

Due to our catastrophic insurance requirements, all current 8th grade students that are going to enter the 9th grade in 2020, will STILL be required to get a PPE for the 2020-2021 school year. All other high school students entering grades 10, 11 & 12 grades that have the PPE paperwork for 2019-2020 school year, can use that physical for the 2020-2021 school year.

Holdrege Elementary School
May 4 at 7:04 PM ·

Elementary Families: Our next round of work packet pick up and drop off is Thursday, May 7 from 8:00 am-12:00 pm, 1:00 pm-3:00 pm, and 5:00 pm-7:00 pm. On Friday, May 8 it will be from 8:00 am-12:00 pm. We will also be available on Monday, May 11 from 5:00 pm to 7:00 pm.

In addition to work packets we will also be sending home any artwork that students have done in art class. If you have any library books or text books at home please bring those back so we can get them checked back in.

We appreciate the work that students have been doing at home and returning to the teachers. Not only does it help keep students engaged in learning and reinforcing skills they've learned, but it's a way that the teachers are staying connected to their individual students. Be well and stay safe!

Phelps County Christian Charity Fund
Caring For Our Community…

Caring Cupboard
Mt. Calvary hosts the Caring Cupboard and Phelps County Ministerial Association Charity Fund.

The Christian Charity Fund helps families in need financially.

The Caring Cupboard is a food and paper pantry that supplements the Phelps County Food Pantry.

Both are open on Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 10 a.m. – noon.

To request help during the COVID-19 pandemic:

Please call Mt. Calvary at 995-2208 between 10 a.m and noon.

Or

Fill out the necessary form online here: http://mtcalvaryholdrege.org/christian-charity-form/

Once the form is submitted our volunteers will fill the request the next business day and call you when the items are ready. When you receive a call letting you know the items are ready, come to Mt. Calvary Lutheran church and pick the items up at west doors.

The link to the website is: http://mtcalvaryholdrege.org/care/

post_text:
Beautiful Windows Brighten Holdrege!

Several artists in Holdrege armed with brushes have illuminated our town with bright window paintings. Holdrege senior, Emily Gustafson, has painted six of the windows so far with more requests in line from local businesses. Generally, each business has an idea of what they want painted: a theme to inspire the community in these difficult times.

Emily has been president of Holdrege’s National Art Honor Society for the past two years and takes her induction pledge seriously: “I will in my life to the best of my ability through my talents in art help to create a more beautiful world for myself, for humankind and for all living things.” Watch for more brightly colored windows in the near future and, as it says in the Sweeney Wealth Management window, let’s “stay strong”.

Check out Emily's work at the following locations:
Sweeney Wealth Management
Spirit of Grace
Salon 31
Holdrege Soft Water
The 308 Boutique
Stephanie’s

Thanks to high school Art instructor, Nancy Wiese for sharing this information and pictures!

Holdrege Elementary School
April 20 at 2:17 PM ·

We hope that you are all staying healthy and safe. We are missing our Holdrege Elementary students very much and wish we could be seeing each of them at school every day. But we have been working hard on getting our next round of work packets ready. We have also been packing up all the student desks with their personal items.

Our next round of packet pick up and drop off will be Thursday, April 23 at the following times: 8 a.m. to 12 p.m., 1 p.m. to 3 p.m., and 5 p.m to 7 p.m. On Friday, April 24, it will be from 8 a.m. to 12 p.m. You can come when it is convenient for you during these times.

You can drop off completed work and pick up a new packet, along with student desk items and your class composite picture if you purchased one. Please write your child's name on the outside of the packet or work to make sorting easier. Thank you.

We will be streaming a Virtual Honors Night on May 11 at 7:00 as well as a Virtual Graduation on May 17 at 2:00 on our Striv.tv channel: https://striv.tv/channel/holdrege/. Please share this link with anyone without social media so they can make sure their internet is sufficient to watch a video from our channel. If someone has issues with watching a video from our channel, they should contact their Internet Service Provider.

Check out the Aurora vs. Holdrege GBB game "On Demand." Thanks to Dean from KUVR for the play by play!

Thanks and Go Dusters!

"Seniors of @HoldregeDusters
Class of 2020...I felt the need to talk to you regarding our plans for your graduation. I’m not going to lie, this was a tough one for me. #imnotcryingYOUREcrying Please watch the video for more details."

Seniors have already been emailed this video as well as other information regarding graduation. We will be doing a "Virtual" graduation on May 17th at 2:00 p.m. on our Striv channel. We plan to do a "Live" graduation on July 25th at 10:00 a.m. Please watch the video from Mr. Hilyard for more details.
